    • Method Detail

      • connect

        Transaction connect(java.lang.Object aActor)
             throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Connects an <<Actor>> to this Package's resource manager.
        Parameters:
        aActor - A object examined by the resource manager to determine and track changes to resources. Each concrete implementation determines what is required to be passed. The Base implementation allows any object to be the actor.
        Returns:
        An Tx instance or null when the Tx cannot be created, such as the connection to the resource manager isn't available.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - The resource manager rejects the actor for some reason, such as the wrong type of object has been passed, the actor's credentials are rejected, or the actor is not authorized for this package.
